Introduction 	  Is there a way to define life ? Scientifically, there is an actual definition of life. Living organisms must have certain characteristics. If they do not have these characteristics, are they living? This butterfly, like all other insects, animals, plants, and every other living organism, shares common characteristics with all life. What exactly does it mean to be alive? The Introduction to Biology chapter will answer this question. These lessons will serve as an introduction to biology, discussing basic Fundamental Concepts of Science and the Chemistry of Life. 
