Geologic  Time  Scale 	  Another tool for understanding the history of Earth and its life is the geologic time scale, shown in Figure 5.5. The geologic time scale divides Earth’s history into divisions (such as eons, eras, and periods) that are based on major changes in geology, climate, and the evolution of life. It organizes Earth’s history and the evolution of life on the basis of important events instead of time alone. It also allows more focus to be placed on recent events, about which we know the most. 
