Summary 	  • Like all organisms, plants detect and respond to stimuli in their environment. Their main response is to change how they grow. • Plant responses are controlled by hormones. Some plant responses are tropisms. • Plants also respond to daily and seasonal cycles and to disease. Use this resource to answer the questions that follow. • Plant tropic Responses at URL l . 
